<h1>@HI{{dou}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @N{{}}<strong>@HI{{dou}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{dou}}</strong> is an interrogative adverb which is used to inquire about a state or a way of doing something..
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{o@KJ{{mother}}sanha<strong>dou</strong>desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      How is your mother?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
@HI{{ikaga}} is the polite version of <strong>@HI{{dou}}</strong> .
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{dou}}</strong> can be used to make an offer.
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{dou}}</strong> can be used to ask how to do something. @HI{{ikaga}} is not
normally used in this case.
</p>

<p>
The idiomatic expression @HI{{doushite}} is used to ask about manner, reason or causes. The reply should
normally end in @HI{{kara}} ("because").
</p>

